<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-19T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-19T02:00:00-05:00" n="615" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d615">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">647.003/326: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sydney</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-19T17:00:00+10:00">November 19, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received November 19—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>All tariff increases tabled May 22nd have been temporarily validated
                                until December 1st. Meanwhile the Government has once again
                                postponed the debate on its trade diversion program<note n="33" xml:id="d615fn33">In his telegram of December 4, 1936, 9 a.m.,
                                    the Consul at Sydney informed the Department that the Australian
                                    Government’s trade diversion policy had been passed through all
                                    stages by both Houses of Parliament (647.006/58).</note> as it
                                believes that within the next few days it will be able to announce a
                                satisfactory settlement of its dispute with Japan.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moffat</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>